snippet.textDisplay: The scoreline may not suggest it, but this was one of Liverpool's most dominant performances in the season. They controlled the game for 90 minutes and were solid everywhere in the field, but what I really want to compliment was their accurate passes and their ability to break down a well-organized defense. Sheffield is the third-best defense so far in the Premier League. A performance like this can increase their chances against Atletico, which I think is the perfect team to expose Liverpool's weaknesses.

snippet.textDisplay: An embarrassing performance by Sheffield United.  One of the strangest things in football is watch teams sit and defend while down by one or two.  Today, Liverpool weren't good at all.  Their crosses were awful, Firmino couldn't make a pass, and they were poor in the final third.  People want to say how good Liverpool are, but that wasn't really the case.  It was more Sheffield looking as if they didn't want to play.  That's why the likes of Dyche, Wilder, and the park the bus English managers will never get a chance to manage a big side.  Big teams aren't content to defend for 70% of the game.
